-- New York MTA May Borrow as Much as $4.8 Billion for Sandy Work
-- B y   E s m é   E .   D e p r e z
-- 2012-11-28T18:08:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-28/new-york-mta-may-borrow-as-much-as-4-8-billion-for-sandy-work.html
The New York Metropolitan
Transportation Authority said it may borrow as much as $4.8
billion to pay for damages from superstorm Sandy.  The short-term debt would be repaid with expected
reimburshements from insurance companies and the  Federal
Emergency Management Agency , transit officials said today at a
board meeting in New York.  The MTA operates the New York City region’s subways, buses,
commuter rail lines and some bridges and tunnels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Esme E. Deprez in New York at 
 edeprez@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark Schoifet at 
 mschoifet@bloomberg.net  